Bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE)2 is the bovine analog to variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease in humans, scrapie in sheep, chronic wasting disease in elk and deer, feline spongiform encephalopathy in cats, and transmissible mink encephalopathy. The causative agents of these transmissible spongiform encephalopathies are infectious proteins, the so-called prions
